### **Summary of Appendix C**

* Pressure-gradient mechanics and orbital dynamics are identical phenomena.
* The universal orbital law (v=(c/k)\sqrt{R/r}) spans atomic to galactic scales.
* The mutual-eclipse formulation replaces (G) with measurable geometry ((R, r, P₀, ρ)).
* Compound occlusion explains clustering and the appearance of gravitation.
* All dynamics remain mechanical, local, and pressure-driven—no field curvature, no attraction-at-a-distance, no dark sector.

